  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.7.0-stable\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ncontract.allEvents({fromBlock: 0, toBlock: 'pending'}).get(callback)\r\nreturns logs for the contract in both the blockchain and pending transactions\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nReturns an empty list in 1.7\r\nHangs in busy loop in 1.6\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\nfunc (f *Filter) unindexedLogs(ctx context.Context, end uint64) ([]*types.Log, error) {\r\nin eth/filters/filter.go#178\r\nf.begin = 0 and int64(end) = -2 (the pending enum) so loop doesn't execute\r\n\r\nIn Geth 1.6 the loop is\r\nfunc (f *Filter) getLogs(ctx context.Context, start, end uint64) (logs []*types.Log, blockNumber uint64, err error) {\r\nin eth/filters/filter.go#170\r\nstart = 0 and end = uint64(-2) so loop doesn't terminate",
