    "body": "It looks like `toBlock: 'latest'` gets away with it because of a check in `func (f *Filter) Logs(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.Log, error)`.  In that function there is a check to replace `-1` ('latest') here:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\tif f.begin == -1 {\r\n\t\tf.begin = int64(head)\r\n\t}\r\n\tend := uint64(f.end)\r\n\tif f.end == -1 {\r\n\t\tend = head\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm new here, so I definitely could be wrong, but it seems like 'pending' doesn't actually have a block number properly assigned to it.  So, those conditional checks in `Logs` could probably just be modified to check for -1 or -2.  Does that sound right?\r\n\r\nIf that seems reasonable I could open up a pull request to fix that.",
